f gotten this spell long ago. What do you all think?  I think this would bring us more utility with out being something that would restrict us to &quot;buff bitch&quot; like so many of us fear.  Lets pester the Dev department to add a &quot;Knock&quot; type spell for wizards in the up comming expansions! <p><br><center><b>Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21704">Legolos</a> Spellbynder |  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21727">Uggliey</a> Bugger<br>LvL 65 Arcanist | LvL 56 Revenant<br>
Of the <a href="http://www.prexuseq.com">Prexus</a> Server</b><br><img src="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/2334867.jpg"></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 9:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> That would be more in line for an enchanter spell IMO.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aauminki>Aauminki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 12:10 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> Knock would be good, after all wizards <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>are</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the masters of arcane travel and blink type of spells are neither directional nor able to put you past obstacles... <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=blank>Sage Aauminki Iceblade</a><br><a href=http://www.vazaelle.dk target=blank>Caer Cadarn</a></big><br>Vazaelle Server</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 1:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> the question is... do you want to be unlocking doors on raids? i don't so i don't like the idea... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.ucsc.edu/~arice/pictures/zuratulisig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=legolos>Legolos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 521<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 12:39 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> I'd have no problem unlocking doors at raids, groups.  And how would it be an Enchanter spell?  It's not enchanting an item, it's not twiddling with the mind.  If I recall correctly the Knock spell in effect broke the lock in AD.  It was a spell of power, not minor manipulation.   Rogues would still be best suited for the job of picking locks, but it would also give people anther option for groups and raids if they are lacking rogues.  Can't even begin to count the number of HS groups I had to disband because we couldn't find a replacment rogue.  And that's just one of MANY instances where this ability would help out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 1:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> Funny - all of the times my HS groups broke up were when the evaccer had to leave.  (Same with the Hole, ToFS, Mephits, etc.) <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=legolos>Legolos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 524<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 9:27 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> Then I can say you didn't try to find one too hard.  You have 2 classes that can evac.  And both classes outnumber rogues,  druids I'd say 2 to 1. <p><br><center><b>Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21704">Legolos</a> Spellbynder |  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21727">Uggliey</a> Bugger<br>LvL 65 Arcanist | LvL 56 Revenant<br>
Of the <a href="http://www.prexuseq.com">Prexus</a> Server</b><br><img src="http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-4/165760/VHFYFZCUIUHSHVKQZXJR-Crit.jpg" width=223 height=15><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 11:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> Yeah, but they were all always too busy soloing for mad xp and cash to join a group (and then posting to the message boards about how unwanted they were in their downtime).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seriously, though, I do think it's fair to have access to some places restricted to certain classes.  (For instance, Hate and Sky.)  It makes sense to have some redundecies, perhaps.  But if so, bards would be a more consistant class to give lockpicking roles to.<br>
<br>
I'm admittedly biased - I just don't want to see rogues lose what little roguishness we have.  Personally, I started my character expecting the sorts of non-combat, non-magical utility you find in D&amp;D rogues/thieves - many of us did.  EQ doesn't support that very well, though, so we reluctantly accepted high melee damage as a consolation.  I'm thrilled when I am actually called on to pick a lock.  ::shrug:: <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=legolos>Legolos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 529<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 12:15 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Knock!</span><hr size=1> Can understand that, and if they made Bards lock picking skills worth a damn I might not of even brought this up.  But bards are fairly rare also, atleast at the high end on my server.  And It's one of those few things I've always viewed a wizard as able to do, long before EQ was around.  Ah well... <p><br><center><b>Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21704">Legolos</a> Spellbynder |  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21727">Uggliey</a> Bugger<br>LvL 65 Arcanist | LvL 56 Revenant<br>
